            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A bibliography written by IA in which he lists 260 (+) of
                     his works and 70 of his teachers. It was written for a sultan, variously known
                     as al-Muẓaffar or al-Muʿaẓẓam Bahāʾ al-Dīn or Shihāb al-Dīn Ghāzī b. al-Malik
                     al-ʿĀdil, in 632H in Damascus.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY cites 16 mss, although none can be considered historic.
                  There are several ‘families’: one is represented by Koprulu 766 (dated by TRF as
                  632H but we have not been able to find evidence for this); another by Princeton
                  Garrett 4098 (dated 949H) and Zahiriyya 4679 (dated 1305); and the third by
                  Badawi’s edition (and other printed editions). There is also a hybrid, Shehit Ali
                  2796 (undated), connected to the library of M. b. Qayṣar who was the head of SQ’s
                  zāwiya. The principal factor in verifying this text as by IA is textual, i.e. its
                  correspondence with Fihris muʿallafāt (RG142) and the corpus of known IA
                  works.</note>
